annotationA: Myotubularin, isoform A; Phosphatidylinositol-3-phosphatase activity; protein binding; protein tyrosine/serine/threonine phosphatase activity; protein tyrosine phosphatase activity. It is involved in the biological process described with: dephosphorylation; protein dephosphorylation; cortical actin cytoskeleton organization; endocytic recycling; mitotic cell cycle; cell projection assembly; chromosome segregation; response to wounding; Belongs to the protein-tyrosine phosphatase family. Non-receptor class myotubularin subfamily
annotationB: Phosphatidylinositide phosphatase SAC1; Phosphoinositide phosphatase that hydrolyzes PtdIns(3)P and PtdIns(4)P. Has low activity towards PtdIns(3,5)P2 (By similarity)
